Cleaning spp names (must be ID’d to species!)

```r
#unique species names
spp_shelf <- dat_SHELF[,unique(spp)]


#Using taxize package, I'm going to check and standardize species scientific names
result.long <- spp_shelf %>%
gnr_resolve(data_source_ids = c(9,155), #marine species and fisebase sources
            with_canonical_ranks=T)

result.long <- data.table(result.long)

#delete repeats and get weird of weird ones


dat_SHELF$spp <- gsub(\Astropecten verilli\, \Astropecten verrilli\, dat_SHELF$spp) #won't come up for some reason, ignore for now
dat_SHELF$spp <- gsub(\Chrysaora fuscens\, \Chrysaora fuscescens\, dat_SHELF$spp)

#unique species names again
spp_shelf <- dat_SHELF[,unique(spp)]

#run long again


#Using taxize package, I'm going to check and standardize species scientific names
result.long <- spp_shelf %>%
gnr_resolve(data_source_ids = c(9,155), #marine species and fisebase sources
            with_canonical_ranks=T)

result.long <- data.table(result.long)

#checked, only genus only spp are graded lower than 0.98

result.short <- result.long[result.long[, .I[which.max(score)], by=.(user_supplied_name, matched_name2)]$V1][,spp := user_supplied_name][score > 0.75,]

#merge cleaned species names with neus full 
dat_SHELF.clean <- dat_SHELF[result.short, on = \spp\]

year_grid <- data.table(table(dat_SHELF.clean$cell, dat_SHELF.clean$year))

#there are some grid cells with infrequent records, I will delete these
grid_cells_to_exclude <- unique(year_grid[N == 0]$V1)

#delete these grid cells from full data table
dat_shelf.reduced <- dat_SHELF.clean[!cell %in% grid_cells_to_exclude]

#732196 observations left, this should be great

#how many tows (TOW) per cell in a given year

haul_cell_unique <- unique(dat_shelf.reduced[,.(haulid, cell, year)])

shelf_samplingevents_byyear <- haul_cell_unique[,.N, .(year, cell)]

shelf_cells_lessthan3 <- shelf_samplingevents_byyear[N<3,]

cells_to_delete <- unique(shelf_cells_lessthan3[,cell])

dat_shelf.reduced.again <- dat_shelf.reduced[!cell %in% cells_to_delete]

#down to 673516 observations

saveRDS(dat_shelf.reduced.again, "shelf_data_gridded.rds")

Find distance between center of each grid cell

#just need grid cell # and center lat lon for each grid cell 
shelf_grid_cells <- unique(dat_shelf.reduced.again[,.(cell, LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

shelf_grid_cells <- setorder(shelf_grid_cells, cell)

shelf_reg_distances <- distm(shelf_grid_cells[,.(LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

colnames(shelf_reg_distances) <- shelf_grid_cells$cell
rownames(shelf_reg_distances) <- shelf_grid_cells$cell

#reorient to long form 
shelf_reg_distances.l <- melt(as.matrix(shelf_reg_distances), varnames = c("cell1", "cell2"), value.name = "distance(m)") #matrix to data frame
The melt generic in data.table has been passed a matrix and will attempt to redirect to the relevant reshape2 method; please note that reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well. To continue using melt methods from reshape2 while both libraries are attached, e.g. melt.list, you can prepend the namespace like reshape2::melt(as.matrix(shelf_reg_distances)). In the next version, this warning will become an error.
shelf_reg_distances.l <- data.table(shelf_reg_distances.l) #and then to data table
shelf_reg_distances.l <- shelf_reg_distances.l[cell1 > cell2,] # get rid of repetitions and self-comparisons
saveRDS(shelf_reg_distances.l, "shelf_reg_distances.l.rds")
